rComments: Had this professor for my spanish DGD. The spanish program is way too tough. It takes over all your time. In the introductory course, they expect you to speak a much higher level of spanish than possible for a new-to-spanish student. I did not find this prof overly understanding when we could not understand what we were being told to understand.

Heba is one of the best sectional instructors I've ever had. She is really engaging and is passionate about the Spanish language. As long as you participate and attend classes you will be more than set for the exam. She is a fair marker and explains every expectation clearly as she goes along. Heba makes learning Spanish fun and exiting.
She is nice and very helpful.
